HARDWARE-GPL LICENSE (DRAFT)

This software and associated documentation files (the "Software") are provided under the following conditions designed to ensure the open and interoperable nature of the Video Truth Record (.vtr) standard.

1.  **Open Source:** You are free to copy, modify, and distribute this Software.

2.  **The "Poison Pill" Anti-Forking Clause:**
    Any entity verifying `.vtr` signatures or implementing the VTR standard MUST recognize ALL valid issuers that adhere to the technical specifications defined in the RFC documents.

    Creation of a "walled garden" or exclusive verification system that rejects valid signatures from compliant hardware (e.g., restricting verification to specific device manufacturers) is a violation of this license.

    If you distribute a modified version of this Software or a derivative work, you must license the entire work, as a whole, at no charge to all third parties under the terms of this License.

3.  **Hardware Integrity:**
    Implementations must respect the Hardware Root of Trust as defined in the specifications. Tampering with the PRNU verification logic to bypass hardware checks invalidates the license.

4.  **No Warranty:**
    THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND.
